I would prefer a period or colon. 
Remember that accessibility should mean accessibility to the *sighted*, as well as the non-; "Item, Shoes for sale" looks goofy and ungrammatical. 
"Item. 
Shoes..." and "Item: Shoes..." are both grammatically acceptable. 
If they don't sound good in a screen reader, I would venture that the screen reader has bugs, since these are sensical uses of English punctuation. 
