By the way, an old question that didn't get answered (at least if it did I missed it - too much stuff too late at night). 
Does HTML 4.0 allow a graphic to be specified as the image to be used in a UL ? 
Can you do it with CSS or CSS2? 
Yes, you can do that with HTML3.2 and CSS1 by playing with the list-style and list-style-image (either putting an image directly in CSS - if it doesn't convey any semantics - or by putting the image right after the LI, in the markup, and removing the ususal bullet visual with CSS). 
I think TITLE and ALT are redundant on IMG, and using either should be fine (and browser should be ready to look for both in some order) When IMG is in A, the TITLE of the A should describe the target while the ALT (or TITLE) of the IMG should describe the IMG itself. 
